        "biography": {
            "errors": [],
            "value": "Research Agenda\n\nAs board member of the International Association of Public and Non-Profit Marketing, I am currently Chairman of the Latin American Congress of Social Marketing 2022. At he same time, as the founding director of The Lima Neuroinsight Research Lab using EEG and Eyetracking technologies, I am interested in the study of the Wow effect in strategic political communication from the point of view of campaign development, media and direct communication. Similarly, I am interested in the analysis of cases of campaigns.\n\nTeaching philosophy\nI believe that we live in a world with multiple points of view as a result of our origin, culture and values.\nI believe that diversity enriches our experience and makes us more respectful and responsible people towards others. \nI deeply believe that building a better world needs our understanding and comprehension of each human being.\n\nThat is why I believe that learning with people who are different from us teaches us to be better people.\n\nTo achieve this, in my courses, students face challenges together and are incorporated into teams that change with each new project.\n\nMy more recent courses were: research, organization & strategy",
